"ruler (sultan)" is literally in the source (the word sulṭān was already in use long before the 11th century, but it was a generally designation for the one in power, akin to the English term "the authorities", rather than a specific title for a ruler); however, precisely because it is literally in the source, we should probably not, and just have "ruler"
